Dow Chemical Co said a judge onthe New Jersey Superior Court for Monmouth County granted itsMerrell Dow Pharmaceuticals Inc unit a motion for a directedverdict in its favor in a case alleging its morning sicknessdrug, Bendectin, caused a child's birth defects.    Merrell Dow said after plaintiffs had completed theirpresentation of evidence, Judge Marshall Selikoff granted thecompany's motion and discharged the jury on grounds thaplaintiffs did not present evidence showing the drug caused thechild' problems. Reuter&#3;